<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-06-28T12:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-06-28T12:00:00-05:00" n="159" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d159">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">500.A15A4/1196: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the Acting Chairman of the American Delegation (<persName corresp="#p_GHS1" type="to">Gibson</persName>)</hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-06-28T13:00:00-04:00">June
                                        28, 1932—1 p.m.</date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>154. Your 281. I think a short visit by Mr. <persName corresp="#p_KFB1">Kellogg</persName> to Geneva might prove
                                extremely useful and count on you to post him as to the situation in
                                respect to the Conference.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_SHL1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>